HEADWORD: Scutellation
<hw>Scu`tel*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The entire covering, or mode of arrangement, of scales, as on the
legs and feet of a bird.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scutelliform</ent>⟦br⟧
